text: Eszter Köszegi-Asztalos is a former Hungarian long track speed skater, who was active in the 1950s and 1960s. Asztalos represented her nation at the World Allround Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1959, finishing 26th overall. She also competed at other international competitions. Between 1960 and 1967 she competed seven times at the Hungarian Allround Championships, winning the silver medal three times (1959, 1960, 1964, 1965) and the bronze medal twice (1962, 1967). == Records== === Personal records === ==References== ==External links== * Category:Place of birth unknown Category:Date of birth unknown Category:Hungarian female speed skaters Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
